Hey, I just saw your message about the hiking trail. I've actually been there a couple of times, and it's really nice this time of year. The views from the top are worth the climb, especially in the late afternoon when the light hits the valley. Make sure you bring enough water though, because there aren't many spots to refill along the way. I think the whole loop is about 5 miles, so it's a decent workout. Let me know if you want to go together next time. I've been trying to get out more on the weekends. It's a great way to clear my head and disconnect from everything. Anyway, I hope you have a good trip if you end up going this weekend! Let me know how it goes. Oh, and I finally got around to listening to that podcast you recommended. The host has a really engaging style. I binged three episodes on my drive up north.

